<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Spiradiclis tubiflora. A Habitat (the arrow shows the place of growth) B Habit C Stipule D Inflorescence, lateral view E Flower, lateral view F Corolla opened to show floral parts G Capsules, frontal view H Capsules, lateral view I Matured capsules with four valves. Flowers of selected Spiradiclis species, lateral views: J S. longipedunculata K S. fusca L S. malipoensis M S. baishaiensis N S. glabra O S. coccinea. Scale bars: 1 cm (B, D, E, F, K, L, M, N, O); 3 mm (C, G, H, I, J). Photos by Bo Pan, Jing Liu and Lei Wu." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.130.34625.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/327964" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Fig. 2D, E</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Wu, B. M. Wang &amp; B. Pan" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis tubiflora" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tubiflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Spiradiclis tubiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically most similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. glandulosa" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glandulosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">S. glandulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. Wu &amp; Q. R. Liu and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. umbelliformis" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="umbelliformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">S. umbelliformis</emphasis>
